6/ Some people will slam all "crypto" that are not #Bitcoin, calling them "sh*tcoins", for example. I'm not one of these folks. I'm hopeful that some of these other "crypto" projects will produce important social value. That said, they will never be able to do what #Bitcoin does.

4/ The Proof-of-Work protocol is a critical element of what makes #Bitcoin, well Bitcoin. It is a key part of what distinguishes Bitcoin and its multi-faceted global value and use cases as distinct from the 17,000 or so other "crypto" projects which use Proof-of-Stake consensus.

2/ Often mistakenly characterized as simply a speculative investment asset, #Bitcoin is best understood as a technology. It can serve multiple functions: a digital store of value (property); a medium of exchange (currency); and, a decentralized network for "layer 2" applications.
